By Chimezie Godfrey Poised to serve its customers better and improve on their travel experience, United Nigeria Airlines (UNA), has added an Airbus A320 to its fleet. In a statement, Head, Corporate Communications, Achilleus-Chud Uchegbu said wiith this, UNA has increased its flight frequencies inward and outward Lagos, Abuja, Asaba, Owerri and Enugu Airports during the yuletide.   According to him, the increased frequencies will be served with the A320 and ERJ145 respectively. “With the new plane, our customers can now enjoy premium business class services as well as improved cabin services on the economy class. “Our Airbus A320 will operate daily scheduled services to the above listed airports.   “This is as we conclude plans to begin scheduled daily flights to Anambra and Osubi Airports. “Our booking portals on www.flyunitednigeria.com is open for reservations on our Airbus A320 and other services. “We wish our customers the best of the season and a great time on United Nigeria Airlines.